name: propanedioic acid, oxo-, diethyl ester
Reason: 1,3-propanedioic acid, oxo-, diethyl ester has a melting point influenced by functional groups relative to the base melting point of benzene, which is around 5°C. The basic unit for comparison is propane, which has a melting point of -18.0 degrees Celsius. The oxo-functionalities and ester linkage introduce additional rigid structures that can participate in dipole interactions and potentially hydrogen bonding, raising the melting point by about +20°C. The presence of two additional phenyl groups can also contribute to an increase in molecular weight and van der Waals interactions, with an approximate increase of +40°C per group, totaling +80°C.
